<h1 id="create-and-post-depreciation-for-a-fixed-asset-group-by-using-depreciation-books" sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="30">Create and post depreciation for a fixed asset group by using depreciation books</h1>


<p sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">You can calculate depreciation for a group of fixed assets. The calculation is based on the number of days that is defined in the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">Asset group depreciation threshold</strong> field on the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">Fixed assets parameters</strong> page. The following table shows the various formulas that are used to calculate depreciation for asset groups.</p>
<table sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">
<thead>
<tr sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">
<th sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Type of proposal</th>
<th sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Number of days that the asset is used</th>
<th sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Formula</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
