<div class="NOTE" sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="76">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="77">In the journal you can use the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="77">Proposal</strong> function for various proposal types to create transactions for fixed asset groups. Asset group depreciation doesn't apply to proposals of the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="77">Consumption depreciation</strong>, <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="77">Revenue recognition of reserves</strong>, or <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/apac-ind-calculate-post-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="77">Extraordinary depreciation</strong> type.</p>
